---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="bayareaswing — Swing dancing in the SF Bay Area">
  <section class="mb-16 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="font-display text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-brass-dark">
      San Francisco Bay Area
    </p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-5xl font-bold leading-tight md:text-6xl">
      So you want to try swing dancing.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal/85">
      Swing dancing is a family of partner dances born in American
      ballrooms in the 1920s, 30s, and 40s — danced socially every week
      across the Bay Area. This site exists for one reason: to help you
      find your first class.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-6">
      <a
        href="/learn"
        class="inline-block bg-burgundy px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-cream no-underline shadow-sm hover:bg-burgundy-dark"
      >
        Find a lesson →
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Balboa</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-charcoal/85">
        A close-embrace dance built for crowded floors and fast tempos.
        Subtle footwork, deep partner connection, and a smooth quality
        that rewards a lifetime of refinement.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Lindy Hop</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-charcoal/85">
        The original swing dance from Harlem in the late 1920s. Eight-count
        basics, breakaway, and an open frame that makes room for
        improvisation, jazz steps, and aerials.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Collegiate Shag</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-charcoal/85">
        A bouncy, high-energy dance that thrives at fast tempos. Six-count
        single, double, and triple-time variations, often danced in a
        compact closed position.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-3xl border-t border-burgundy/20 pt-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">What to expect at your first lesson</h2>
    <ul class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-charcoal/85">
      <li>
        <strong>You don't need a partner.</strong> Drop-in classes rotate
        partners every minute or two. Show up alone.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Wear what you can move in.</strong> Smooth-soled shoes
        help (avoid rubber soles); jeans are fine. Bring water.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Say hello.</strong> Swing scenes are some of the most
        welcoming dance communities you'll find. Tell people it's your
        first time — they will look out for you.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
